				<wikidot:authorName>TailPipe</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1684764</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Just had to downvote this, I just don't find this interesting. There is one point that irritates me a bit:</p> <blockquote> <p>a used sneaker is to be thrown into SCP-2083, and the results recorded by on-site personnel.</p> </blockquote> <p>Well, the article did say &quot;footwear&quot;, so why not just say &quot;a used shoe&quot;?<br /> Also, I had to add a period that was missing at the end of a sentence, but I feel that there should be a comma in the middle of this sentence:</p> <blockquote> <p>~2% of legs within SCP-2083 appear to have ingrown toenails, but other than this(,) there are no significant health details apparent on any SCP-2083 leg.</p> </blockquote> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
