				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-826584#post-1994924</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-826584/scp-2083#post-1994924</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 20 Mar 2014 07:30:24 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>judgedeadd</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>230496</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>Following this, the feet will appear to retreat into the walls of SCP-2083, although no corresponding leg will appear on the opposite side. The foot will orient sideways, and remain suspended there until the shoe is removed, at which point the leg will return to its former state.</p> </blockquote> <p>I've read this several times and I still cannot comprehend what exactly it means. What retracts into the walls? The foot wearing the shoe? The legs that the foot belongs to? All the other legs? What do you mean by &quot;foot will orient sideways&quot;&#8212;if it has retracted into the wall, how can we know what it does inside the wall? If it didn't retract inside the wall, what does it mean &quot;sideways&quot;? Does the leg's ankle somehow twist sideways painfully? Does the foot detach from the leg and begin floating in mid-air, sideways?</p> <blockquote> <p>1996</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p>SMS text message</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p>contained a picture</p> </blockquote> <p><em>what</em></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
